er part of his reign he paid more attention to his religion than to his kingdom. He died childless, and his death sparked off conflicting claims to his throne, which were resolved by the victory of William the Conqueror at the Battle of Hastings. His memory was honoured by Normans and English alike, for his fairness and his piety. Edward's mother was Norman; he had spent part of his youth in Normandy; and William claimed to have been nominated by Edward as his successor. Edward was canonized in the 12th century, and came to be venerated throughout Europe as a model of a Christian king."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"EDWARD Ewrus was born about 1017, in Normandy, France. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs Edward of Salisbury."},"et":{"about 1017–":"umbes 1017–Surnud","1020–Female":"1020–Surnud","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","1037–1066":"1037–1066","1017–Male":"1017–Surnud","1017":"1017","1037":"1037","about 1017":"umbes 1017","1066":"1066","1020":"1020","about 1037":"umbes 1037","1070":"1070","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Paris, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1017–":"noin 1017–Kuollut","1020–Female":"1020–Kuollut","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","1037–1066":"1037–1066","1017–Male":"1017–Kuollut","1017":"1017","1037":"1037","about 1017":"noin 1017","1066":"1066","1020":"1020","about 1037":"noin 1037","1070":"1070","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska","Paris, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1017–":"environ 1017–Décédé","1020–Female":"1020–Décédée","1070–Female":"1070–Décédée","1037–1066":"1037–1066","1017–Male":"1017–Décédé","1017":"1017","1037":"1037","about 1017":"environ 1017","1066":"1066","1020":"1020","about 1037":"environ 1037","1070":"1070","Normandy, France":"Normandie, France","Paris, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, France","lifeSummary":"EDWARD Ewrus est né environ 1017, à Normandie, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs Edward of Salisbury."},"de":{"about 1017